data.title: HighRadius offers $0 Implementation Fee, $0 Subscription Fee via Outcome Based Pricing for oCFO Software; pay only based on gains.
data.description: HighRadius, a leading provider of AI solutions for Order-to-Cash, Accounts Payable, Record-to-Report, and Treasury processes, has rolled out an innovative pricing model called Outcome Based Pricing (OBP). Under this plan, customers are charged $0 for implementation and subscription until their system is operational. With OBP, clients only pay a portion of their actual financial gains based on the impact on profit and loss statements. This marks a significant shift in pricing strategy for HighRadius, with over 190 AI agents available, providing a unique approach to cost transparency for customers.

data.title: Duolingo stock sinks as company shifts focus towards free learner experience, with bookings surpassing $1 billion in 2025. Morgan Stanley downgrades stock and slashes price target to $100 from $245. CEO emphasizes user growth strategy.
data.description: Duolingo Inc. (NASDAQ: DUOL) shares are down in premarket trading after their recent earnings report revealed strong user growth but a shift towards enhancing the free learner experience. Major firms like Morgan Stanley have downgraded the stock to Equal Weight and cut price forecasts from $245 to $100 due to concerns about the company's growth trajectory. Despite the stock decline, Duolingo reported surpassing 50 million daily active users and generating over $1 billion in bookings for the first time in 2025. CEO Luis von Ahn highlighted the importance of focusing on user growth and improving the free learner experience in 2026, which may impact near-term financial growth. Duolingo aims to prioritize teaching better and expanding into new learning areas like chess, math, and music. This strategic shift comes as advances in AI are reshaping how people learn.
